/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1787:"<p>We recently released a security update to W3 Total Cache that addresses a vulnerability that can be exploited on misconfigured servers when database caching to disk is enabled. All users are encouraged to update.</p>
<p>If you see the following error following the upgrade:
<pre class="crayon-plain-tag">Fatal error: Call to undefined function w3_is_dbcluster() in /path/to/wp-content/some-file.php</pre></p>
<p>This likely means that you&#8217;ve had us configure W3 Total Cache on your site already, and you were running a newer version of the plugin already. </p>
<p>You&#8217;ll need to manually disable W3 Total Cache to restore access and <a href="http://www.w3-edge.com/contact/">reach out</a> so we can get you sorted.</p>
